last_episode_to_air.overview: Murdered in broad daylight, everyone wants to know what happened to teenagers Abby Williams and Libby German. Who is the Delphi killer? "IMPACT x Nightline" goes inside the trial of the man charged with their brutal deaths.

name: Impact x Nightline
overview: Each week, ABC News’ correspondents will leave the anchor desk and studios behind, taking viewers on a journey straight to the source of the stories everyone is talking about, plus the ones no one has even heard of yet. The program’s timely reporting will dive deep into the issues driving the conversations across America and spotlight real people affected by current events featuring hard-hitting investigative reports and profiles of newsmakers from around the globe.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: ABC News’ correspondents are taking viewers on a journey straight to the source of the stories.

episodes.name: AFTERMATH: The Dobbs Effect
episodes.overview: The stakes have never been higher. Since the Supreme Court reversed Roe v. Wade, states are implementing bans and rolling back laws. But, when it comes to the polarizing topic of abortion, things aren't always as black.

episodes.name: Before Columbine & Climate Conservatives
episodes.overview: The case study of a high school shooting 25 years later, plus the unlikely hero of the climate change movement.

episodes.name: Caffeine Jungle
episodes.overview: What's behind those little stamps that leave big impressions? Journey to the remote highlands of Chiapas, Mexico as we explore the world of ethically certified coffee there.

episodes.name: The Bodies of Lake Mead & Make-Believe Backlash
episodes.overview: Why do bodies keep popping up in Lake Mead? And the world of make believe is getting more diverse. Not everybody's happy about it

episodes.name: Threat to Democracy & 48 Hours With Charlie Puth
episodes.overview: Civic workers are under attack-- how it threatens our democracy. And behind the scenes with Charlie Puth. The TikTok sensation and musical savant says he’s a “definite dork.”

episodes.name: Ye: It All Falls Down
episodes.overview: Exploring the controversy around Ye, formerly known as Kanye West. His antisemitic comments sparked a firestorm, but what's the conversation missing? We dig in.

episodes.name: Weekend with Weezy
episodes.overview: 72 hours with rap great Lil Wayne in his New Orleans hometown. He opens up about his mental health, growing up a child star and when fans might finally hear "Tha Carter VI".

episodes.name: Taylor Swift's Ticketmaster
episodes.overview: We're breaking down the anatomy of a ticketing fiasco after Taylor Swift's "The Eras" tour seemed to break the platform. Plus, inside the booming business of nostalgia and why retro games are back in style.

episodes.name: Killer Curves
episodes.overview: From the hyper-popular BBL to illegal augmentation injections, the lengths some are taking to achieve the bouncing bottom of their dreams are explored.

episodes.name: Into the Deep With "Avatar"
episodes.overview: We take viewers on a never-before-seen journey behind the scenes of the highly-anticipated film Avatar: The Way of Water. 13 years later, we sit down with the cast and director James Cameron to talk about the barriers this movie is still breaking.

episodes.name: Megan Thee Stallion & The Trial of Tory Lanez
episodes.overview: We examine the case of Tory Lanez, the rapper convicted of shooting superstar Megan Thee Stallion. Why it seemed like she was the one on trial and what this case says about how we treat survivors of violence.

episodes.name: The Housewife’s Scam: The REAL Life of Jen Shah
episodes.overview: The star of the Real Housewives of Salt Lake City, Jen Shah, now sentenced to 6.5 years in prison for running a massive fraud scheme. How did she pull it off? For the first time, IMPACT talks with victims whose lives were destroyed by Shah’s scams.

episodes.name: The Year That Crypto Broke
episodes.overview: A look at the makers and breakers of a volatile year in the cryptocurrency world and whether the industry will be able to pick itself back up again.

episodes.name: Football City, USA
episodes.overview: Michael Strahan travels to the South Carolina city that says it pumps out more football players per capita than anywhere else.

episodes.name: The Boys Are Back: 24 Hours With the Jonas Brothers
episodes.overview: It's been almost four years since Kevin, Joe and Nick released an album; now, the Jonas Brothers are back, and Juju Chang is behind the scenes with exclusive access; they catch up on their lives, their wives, and why they almost broke up for good.

episodes.name: Under His Spell: Sarah Lawrence Dad Turned Predator
episodes.overview: The case that horrified the country; a dad moved into his daughter's dorm at Sarah Lawrence College; for about ten years, Lawrence Ray violated, extorted and sex trafficked her friends and others; disturbing recordings and the survivors' stories.

episodes.name: The Skinny Shot
episodes.overview: Drugs like Ozempic and Mounjaro seem to have everyone buzzing about the possibility of weight loss in a few months; they're FDA-approved to treat diabetes; now, recent shortages have some questioning priorities about who should get the drug.

episodes.name: Model Behavior
episodes.overview: With old shows getting new life on streaming, one show is getting heat: America's Next Top Model; past contestants and judge Janice Dickinson join the show; supermodel Coco Rocha teaches pose, poise and how aspiring models can protect themselves.

episodes.name: Famous Fake-Outs
episodes.overview: America's history is littered with those who lie and defraud; some of the most well-known liars are freshman Congressman George Santos and fake heiress Anna Delvey.

episodes.name: Paris Hilton: In Her Own Words
Cashing In: The Debate Over Paying College Athletes
Who Shot Tupac?
episodes.overview: In the first episode of the new season, ABC News multiplatform reporter Ashan Singh documents the life of legendary rapper Tupac Shakur on the 27th anniversary of his death and the unsolved drive-by shooting that killed him. Through examination of newly released body camera footage from a police raid in his murder investigation, the program looks at where his case stands today and why so many conspiracy theories exist about his death. The program features interviews with Leila Steinberg, Shakur’s first manager; Danyel Smith, former music journalist and friend of Shakur; Chris Carroll, a police officer who responded to the scene the night of Shakur’s shooting; and reporters who followed Shakur’s career closely, including Cathy Scott and Kevin Powell, who touch on Shakur’s enduring legacy on hip-hop and American culture. Are police any closer to solving one of pop culture’s most mysterious unsolved murders?

episodes.name: Lizzo's Legal Limbo
episodes.overview: Lizzo is under fire; she's being sued by three former dancers and a designer; Lizzo denies it all.

episodes.name: Ruby Franke: A Momfluencer's Double Life?
episodes.overview: Momfluencer" Ruby Franke came to fame as a Mormon mom and influencer known for her parenting style.

episodes.name: Divorcing Jonas - Joe & Sophi
episodes.overview: Joe Jonas and Sophie Turner are the latest to split in a bombshell Hollywood divorce.

episodes.name: Sextortion
episodes.overview: Sextortion" is a cybercrime involving eliciting explicit photos from online victims for blackmail.

episodes.name: Unboxing Shein
episodes.overview: As the biggest clothing brand on the Internet, Shein makes other fast fashion companies look slow. They can’t seem to stay out of the headlines, but that doesn’t seem to be stopping the shopping.

episodes.name: It's Britney
episodes.overview: In her memoir "The Woman in Me," pop icon Britney Spears lays bare her heartaches and traumas.

episodes.name: Natalee Holloway: A Killer Confesses
episodes.overview: Natalee Holloway's family's search for answers and the haunting confession of her killer.

episodes.name: The Situation - Drugs & Sex on the Jersey Shore
episodes.overview: The Situation" reveals a dark addiction battle, holding nothing back on his hard-partying past.

episodes.name: Taylor Swift & Travis Kelce - The Pop Star & The NFL Player
episodes.overview: Digging into a relationship that seems to be the stuff of legend, combining two massive fan bases.

episodes.name: Reality Reckoning? Bethenny Frankel's Fight for Change
episodes.overview: Bethenny Frankel, Leah McSweeney and Nick Thompson describe an industry they say is toxic.

episodes.name: On the Brink
episodes.overview: Diane Sawyer and Rachel Scott share the dire impact of new healthcare limitations on pregnant women

episodes.name: OnlyFans: Not Just Sex
episodes.overview: A new wave of OnlyFans creators are cashing in, without taking it all off; from "Sopranos" star Drea de Matteo, to a comedian who's made more than a million dollars, there's a lucrative other side of OnlyFans that's about more than sex.

episodes.name: Dance Moms: Behind the Curtain
episodes.overview: Thirteen years since its debut, the moms and dancers reflect on their ups and downs from their time on the competition; Abby Lee Miller tells all.

episodes.name: Diddy's Downfall
episodes.overview: Sean "Diddy" Combs was one of the most powerful men in music; the entrepreneur is facing multiple lawsuits and is under investigation for criminal sex-trafficking; insiders paint a picture of the embattled star and explore the mogul's downfall.

episodes.name: The Secrets of the 2x2 Church
episodes.overview: In a secretive religious sect that sends leaders into homes, disturbing allegations swirl; hundreds say they were sexually abused as children; now the FBI is investigating.

episodes.name: SCOTT PETERSON- THE WRONG MAN?
episodes.overview: For 20 years, Scott Peterson has been behind bars, found guilty of murdering his pregnant wife Laci and their unborn son. Could evidence brought to light by the Los Angeles Innocence Project set one of America's most notorious convicted killers free?

episodes.name: What Happened to Matthew Perry?
episodes.overview: After the sudden death of beloved actor Matthew Perry, a web of drug dealing and greed is revealed. Five people now arrested and charged in his death. We take you inside the world of ketamine and the final days of Perry’s life.

episodes.name: Killer Mom - The Case of Susan Smith
episodes.overview: Susan Smith drowned her two young boys, then falsely accused a Black man of carjacking and kidnapping them. Thirty years later, she's now eligible for parole. Despite Smith's crimes and bad behavior behind bars, could she walk free?

episodes.name: Diddy: Drugs, Lies & Freak Offs
episodes.overview: Freak offs", drugs, and sex trafficking allegations are at the center of a shocking indictment against hip-hop mogul Sean “Diddy” Combs. The investigation into the alleged criminal enterprise facilitating sex crimes. Could Diddy be locked up for life?

episodes.name: BEHIND THE BLIND SIDE - TACKLING THE TRUTH
episodes.overview: The Blind Side made Michael Oher famous. Now, the former NFL player claims that he was blindsided by the family that took him in. How did such a feel-good story end up mired in a contentious legal battle?

episodes.name: Rock & Roll Hall of Fame
episodes.overview: Looks at the 2024 class of Inductees, explores the evolution of one of the music industry's most prestigious honors, and unpacks the nomination process with music industry experts and legends leading up to this year's ceremony.

episodes.name: Menendez Brothers: Monsters or Victims?
episodes.overview: They killed their parents- but now there’s a push to free them. New evidence and a re-examination of the Menendez family’s alleged dark secrets are giving the brothers newfound support. IMPACT investigates as their story once again captivates the nation.

episodes.name: One Direction: Liam Payne’s Final Days
episodes.overview: Drugs, a trashed hotel room, and a deadly fall: How One Direction’s Liam Payne tragically died. The boy band singer’s sudden death sparked renewed questions about the dark side of fame. How did the 31-year-old’s brilliant star fade so dramatically?

episodes.name: Stealing Graceland
episodes.overview: When news broke that Graceland would be foreclosed, fans were shocked. Could it be possible? Through new interviews with those closely connected with the iconic Presley family landmark and untold stories from actress Riley Keough's new memoir detailing her mother's, Lisa Marie Presley, experience growing up there, "IMPACT x Nightline" takes viewers inside Graceland to investigate the shocking alleged foreclosure scheme that many worried had a chance to succeed.

episodes.name: Who is the Delphi killer?
episodes.overview: Murdered in broad daylight, everyone wants to know what happened to teenagers Abby Williams and Libby German. Who is the Delphi killer? "IMPACT x Nightline" goes inside the trial of the man charged with their brutal deaths.
